{{Coord|43|44|4.74|N|7|25|16.8|E|scale:1563_type:landmark_region:MC|display=title}} {{Infobox Grand Prix race report | Type = F1 | Country = Monaco | Grand Prix = Monaco | Date = 26 May | Year = 1974 | Image = Circuit de Monaco 1973.png | Caption = Circuit de Monaco | Official name = XXXII [[Monaco Grand Prix|Grand Prix de Monaco]] | Location = [[Monte Carlo]], Monaco | Course = Street Circuit | Course_km = 3.278 | Course_mi = 2.037 | Distance_laps = 78 | Distance_km = 255.684 | Distance_mi = 158.886 | Pole_Driver = [[Niki Lauda]] | Pole_Country = AUT | Pole_Team = [[Scuderia Ferrari|Ferrari]] | Pole_Time = 1:26.3<ref name="LangVol3P31">{{cite book | last = Lang | first = Mike | title = Grand Prix! Vol 3 | publisher = Haynes Publishing Group | date = 1983 | isbn = 0-85429-380-9 | page = 31}}</ref> | Fast_Driver = [[Ronnie Peterson]] | Fast_Team = [[Team Lotus|Lotus]]-[[Ford Motor Company|Ford]] | Fast_Time = 1:27.9<ref name="LangVol3P33">{{cite book | last = Lang | first = Mike | title = Grand Prix! Vol 3 | publisher = Haynes Publishing Group | date = 1983 | isbn = 0-85429-380-9 | page = 33}}</ref> | Fast_Lap = 57 {{smaller|(lap record)}} | Fast_Country = SWE | First_Driver = [[Ronnie Peterson]] | First_Country = SWE | First_Team = [[Team Lotus|Lotus]]-[[Ford Motor Company|Ford]] | Second_Driver = [[Jody Scheckter]] | Second_Country = South Africa | Second_flag_suffix = 1928 | Second_Team = [[Tyrrell Racing|Tyrrell]]-[[Ford Motor Company|Ford]] | Third_Driver = [[Jean-Pierre Jarier]] | Third_Country = FRA | Third_Team = [[Shadow Racing Cars|Shadow]]-[[Ford Motor Company|Ford]] }}
The '''1974 Monaco Grand Prix''' was a [[Formula One]] [[motor race]] held at [[Circuit de Monaco|Monaco]] on 26 May 1974. It was race 6 of 15 in both the [[1974 World Championship of Drivers]] and the [[1974 International Cup for Formula One Manufacturers]]. The 78-lap race was won by [[Team Lotus|Lotus]] driver [[Ronnie Peterson]] after he started from third position. [[Jody Scheckter]] finished second for the [[Tyrrell Racing|Tyrrell]] team and [[Shadow Racing Cars|Shadow]] driver [[Jean-Pierre Jarier]] came in third.
