The '''1981 enlargement of the European Communities''' was the second enlargement of what is now the [[European Union]], then the European Communities (EC). [[Greece]] acceded to the EEC on 1 January 1981. It is considered a part of the [[Enlargement of the European Union#Mediterranean enlargements|Mediterranean enlargement]].

[[File:EC10-1981 European Community map enlargement.svg|thumb|EC-9+Greece]]

