[[Image:Progressive Bahrain.jpg|thumb|right|240px|An overview of Bahrain]]
The '''Bahrain light rail network''' is a public transport project in [[Bahrain]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.railwaysafrica.com/blog/2010/04/bahrain%E2%80%99s-184km-planned-network/ |accessdate=2011-02-20 |title=BAHRAIN’S 184KM PLANNED NETWORK |publisher=Railways Africa |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110715151655/http://www.railwaysafrica.com/blog/2010/04/bahrain%E2%80%99s-184km-planned-network/ |archivedate=2011-07-15 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bahrain.com/logistics-and-infrastructure.aspx |accessdate=2011-02-20 |title=Bahrain logistics and infrastructure, the trading hub of the Gulf |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100107213531/http://www.bahrain.com/logistics-and-infrastructure.aspx |archivedate=2010-01-07 |df= }}</ref>

==Routes==
Several different lines are planned:<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.projectsandleads.com/campaign/Newsletter/Newsletter_Sep09.html|accessdate=2011-02-20|title=10 Bahrain projects you should get involved in}}</ref>
* Blue Line, from Jufair to the Northern city and [[Budaiya]];
* Brown Line, from Manama to the University and Bahrain Circle;
* Green Line, Jufair to Manama to [[Seef]];
* Orange Line, from the [[Bahrain International Airport|airport]] to [[Diar Island]];
* Pink Line, connecting [[Hamad Town]], [[Riffa]], Isa Town, [[Sitra]], and South Manama;
* Red Line, from the airport through Manama to the [[Qatar Bahrain Causeway|Qatar-Bahrain causeway]].

==Project==
The project was unveiled in 2008, with construction planned to start in 2009.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://english.bna.bh/?ID=73448 |accessdate=2011-02-20 |title=Bahrain News Agency }}{{dead link|date=October 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> However, construction has been repeatedly delayed. By December 2009, construction was expected to start in 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://bahraini.tv/2009/12/22/bahrain-plans-light-rail-network-to-ease-traffic-flow/ |accessdate=2011-02-20 |title=Bahrain Plans Light Rail Network to Ease Traffic Flow |publisher=Bahraini.TV |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110719030652/http://bahraini.tv/2009/12/22/bahrain-plans-light-rail-network-to-ease-traffic-flow/ |archivedate=2011-07-19 |df= }}</ref> Consultants were prequalified in 2010;<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.meed.com/sectors/transport/rail/bahrain-prequalifies-consultants-for-light-rail-study/3005656.article|accessdate=2011-02-20|title=Bahrain prequalifies consultants for light rail study}}</ref> as of January 2010, the project was still awaiting budgetary approval<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.meed.com/sectors/transport/rail/bahrain-awaits-budget-approval-for-light-rail-study/3083208.article|accessdate=2011-02-20|title=Bahrain awaits budget approval for light rail study}}</ref> but it was hoped that construction could begin before the end of 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://sekkah.com/Details.aspx?Page_ID=883 |accessdate=2011-02-20 |title=Sekkah |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110716034810/http://sekkah.com/Details.aspx?Page_ID=883 |archivedate=2011-07-16 |df= }}</ref>{{updateneeded|date=February 2014|reason=Rail transport articles in need of updating}}

The first phase,  including 24&nbsp;km of light rail network, is expected to cost BD453 million. Subsequent phases will cost more.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tradearabia.com/news/stn_178416.html|accessdate=2011-02-20|title=Bahrain's $8bn public transport network on track|quote=Light}}</ref>

