'''Beurre d'Ardenne''' is a type of [[cow]]'s [[milk]] [[Butter]] made in the [[Ardennes]] of [[Belgium]].

As a traditional product of the area it received Belgian [[Protected Geographical Status|appellation d'origine]] by Royal decree in 1984,<ref name="BELDOC">[http://www.wipo.int/clea/fr/details.jsp?id=395 Beurre d'Ardennes AO info]{{dead link|date=November 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }} (French) OMPI Resources</ref> and received European ''PDO'' status in 1996.<ref name="DOOR">[http://ec.europa.eu/agriculture/quality/door/registeredName.html?denominationId=128 Beurre d'Ardennes Profile], European PDO/PGI Database, European Commission</ref>

==Production==
The areas where it is produced are within [[Wallonia]] and include the provinces of [[Luxembourg (Belgium)|Luxembourg]], [[Namur (province)|Namur]] and [[Liège (province)|Liège]].<ref name="APAQWPDF">{{cite web|url=http://www.apaqw.be/files/files/Pdf/Peda/doss/Lesproduitslaitiers_beurre.pdf |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2010-06-28 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100525103244/http://www.apaqw.be/files/files/Pdf/Peda/doss/Lesproduitslaitiers_beurre.pdf |archivedate=2010-05-25 |df= }}, APAQ-W</ref>

To qualify, production must take place entirely in those areas, from milking of the cows, through to [[Churning (butter)|churning]] and, final maturation of the butter,<ref name="APAQW">[http://www.apaqw.be/search.asp?q=barattage Agency for Wallonian Agricultural Produce (APAQ-W) - Butter Product Search] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110706132608/http://www.apaqw.be/search.asp?q=barattage |date=July 6, 2011 }} (French)</ref> and may be made by churning milk, cream or a mixture of both. The final product must be of at least 82% [[butterfat]] and [[butyric acid]].

