{{distinguish|Birgid language}} {{Infobox language |name=Birgit |states=[[Chad]] |region=southeast |speakers={{sigfig|10,400|3}} |date=2000 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Afro-Asiatic |fam2=[[Chadic languages|Chadic]] |fam3=[[East Chadic languages|East Chadic]] |fam4=[[East Chadic B languages|East Chadic B]] |fam5=[[Mubi languages|Mubi]] (B.1.2) |iso3=btf |glotto=birg1239 |glottorefname=Birgit }}
'''Birgit''' (also known as Bergit, Birgid, Berguid) is an [[Afro-Asiatic languages|Afro-Asiatic]] language spoken in southeastern [[Chad]].<ref name=e18/>
