'''John F. Kennedys Plads''' ("[[John F. Kennedy]]'s Square") is located in central [[Aalborg]], Denmark. Dedicated to the 35th [[President of the United States]], it contains a horse and rider statue of [[Christian IX of Denmark]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Christian IX of Denmark - Aalborg, Denmark|url=http://www.waymarking.com/waymarks/WMFFJJ_Christian_IX_of_Denmark_Aalborg_Denmark|work=waymarking.com|accessdate=1 September 2013}}</ref> Reserved for pedestrians, the site is constructed of granite and concrete tiles. [[Aalborg station|Aalborg Train Station]], [[Aalborg Busterminal|Aalborg Bus Terminal]], Kennedy Arcade, and Park Hotel Aalborg are adjacent to the square.

