{{Infobox Radio Station | name = Sunrise FM | image = [https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/1551753290/sunrise_fm_copy.jpg] | city = [[Koforidua]] | area = [[Eastern Region (Ghana)|Eastern region]] | branding = | slogan = Yɛyɛ sono wonko | airdate = | frequency = 106.7&nbsp;MHz,102.1&nbsp;MHz | format = Local news, talk and music | language = [[English language|English]], [[Twi dialect|Twi]] | power = | erp = | class = | callsign_meaning = | owner = [[Ghana Broadcasting Corporation]] | website = [http://www.gbcghana.com/index.php?launch=radio&type=sunrise_fm] }}
'''Sunrise FM''' is a public radio station in [[Koforidua]], the capital town of the [[Eastern Region (Ghana)|Eastern region]] of [[Ghana]].<ref name=Radio/> It is located in Effiduase a suburb of the [[Koforidua]] township. The station is owned and run by the state broadcaster, the [[Ghana Broadcasting Corporation]].<ref name=GBC/><ref name=RW/>
